# Cloudflare Pages — SPA client-side routing fallback.
#
# SPA fallback is handled entirely in code by functions/_middleware.ts,
# not by a rewrite rule in this file. An earlier `/*  /index.html  200`
# rule here was found to interfere with the middleware: the two
# mechanisms appear to run in sequence on this project's deployment path
# (Pages Functions + Workers Builds), and combining a _redirects rewrite
# with the middleware's own asset lookup produced a broken response —
# HTTP 200 with a stray Location header and an empty body — worse than
# the plain 404 this was meant to fix.
#
# Do not add a catch-all rewrite rule here. If routing needs change,
# make them in functions/_middleware.ts instead, where the exact
# request/response handling is fully under our control and testable
# against a real deployment.
